underlying_goal: The user wanted to clean up their Claude Code plugin configuration by removing duplicate marketplaces and plugins.
friction_detail: Claude lacked permissions to remove directories in `~/.claude/`, requiring the user to run the `rm` commands manually. An orphaned plugin reference in settings.json also had to be removed to resolve an uninstallation error.
primary_success: Successfully diagnosed and created a comprehensive plan to clean up a complex, corrupted plugin configuration involving duplicate marketplaces and installations. Claude then executed the plan, safely backing up and editing multiple JSON configuration files to restore the system to a clean state.
brief_summary: The user needed to clean up a messy plugin configuration with duplicate marketplaces. Claude created a detailed plan, backed up all relevant files, and then systematically edited multiple JSON configs to remove duplicates. After guiding the user through the manual deletion of directories, the configuration was successfully cleaned and verified.
